wikipedia_page.main: Brian Arthur Gomm (24 June 1918 - 23 April 1995) was a cricketer and footballer who made two first-class cricket appearances for Somerset in 1939 and played association football for Yeovil in 1936-9 and for West Bromwich Albion in 1939 and 1945-6. He had amateur status in both sports.
